<link href="adcp.css" rel="stylesheet"><entry><xh5>king for a day • king of day, the</xh5><p> <i>king for a day—</i>a person whose fame, popularity, etc., is but short-lived: Superintendent Michael Snow was <u>king for a day</u> in Middlefield this summer, serving as grand marshal of the town’s bicentennial parade.</p><p><i>king of day, the</i>—(poetic) the Sun: I have never seen Italy’s far-famed sky, but I do not think it could surpass that evening sunset. <u>The king of day</u> sinking into the bosom of Silver Lake...</p> </entry>
